#. type: Content of: <section><section><para>
#: en/content/features/chat.xml:11
msgid ""
"The chat feature of <emphasis role=\"bold\">OTRS Business "
"Solution</emphasis>™ allows for chats between agents and customers using the"
" OTRS frontend. Once enabled, customers (or public users) can start chats "
"with agents and vice versa. Finished chats can be archived and attached to "
"tickets, or can be downloaded as PDF by agents, customers and public users."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><para>
#: en/content/features/chat.xml:14
msgid ""
"Each chat is assigned to a chat channel. Chat channels are like chat rooms. "
"Each chat channel is assigned to a certain group which controls the "
"permissions for this channel. If no chat channel is selected when a chat is "
"created, this chat will be created in a default channel (which is "
"automatically created if it doesn't exist)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><title>
#: en/content/features/chat.xml:19
#: en/content/features/dynamicfield-contactwithdata.xml:86
#: en/content/features/dynamicfield-database.xml:27
#: en/content/features/report-generator.xml:16
#: en/content/features/sla-selection-dialog.xml:16
#: en/content/features/ticket-attachment-view.xml:16
#: en/content/features/ticket-timeline-view.xml:16
#: en/content/features/video-calls.xml:21
msgid "Configuration"
msgstr "Konfiguration"

#. type: Content of: <section><section><para>
#: en/content/features/chat.xml:21
msgid ""
"The following SysConfig configuration options are relevant for this feature."
" Please note that you can also define a list of fixed texts which are being "
"displayed to public users and customers in the chat module. For more "
"information on which texts can be changed, please have a look at the module "
"configuration (OTRSBusiness → Core::Chat)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: en/content/features/chat.xml:25 en/content/features/video-calls.xml:27
msgid "ChatEngine::Active"
msgstr "ChatEngine::Active"

#. type: Content of:
#. <section><section><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: en/content/features/chat.xml:28
msgid "Controls whether or not the chat feature is enabled."
msgstr "Konfiguriert ob der Chat aktiviert oder deaktiviert ist."

#. type: Content of: <section><section><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: en/content/features/chat.xml:33
msgid "ChatEngine::ChatDirection::PublicToAgent"
msgstr "ChatEngine::ChatDirection::PublicToAgent"

#. type: Content of:
#. <section><section><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: en/content/features/chat.xml:36
msgid ""
"Controls whether or not public users should be able to start chats (please "
"note that the frontend module configuration for the public chat frontend in "
"<literal>PublicFrontend::Module###PublicChat</literal> has to be enabled, "
"too)."
msgstr "Kontrolliert ob öffentliche Benutzer Chats starten können (bitte beachten Sie, dass das die Modulkonfiguration für das öffentliche Chatmodul in <literal>PublicFrontend::Module###PublicChat</literal> ebenfalls aktiviert sein muss). "

#. type: Content of: <section><section><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: en/content/features/chat.xml:41
msgid "ChatEngine::ChatDirection::CustomerToAgent"
msgstr "ChatEngine::ChatDirection::CustomerToAgent"

#. type: Content of:
#. <section><section><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: en/content/features/chat.xml:44
msgid ""
"Controls whether or not customers should be able to start chats (please note"
" that the frontend module configuration for the customer chat frontend in "
"<literal>CustomerFrontend::Module###CustomerChat</literal> has to be "
"enabled, too)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: en/content/features/chat.xml:49
msgid "ChatEngine::ChatDirection::AgentToCustomer"
msgstr "ChatEngine::ChatDirection::AgentToCustomer"

#. type: Content of:
#. <section><section><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: en/content/features/chat.xml:52
msgid ""
"Controls whether or not agents should be able to start chats with customers "
"directly."
msgstr "Definiert ob Agenten einen Chat zu Kunden initieren dürfen."

#. type: Content of: <section><section><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: en/content/features/chat.xml:57
msgid "ChatEngine::ChatDirection::AgentToAgent"
msgstr "ChatEngine::ChatDirection::AgentToAgent"

#. type: Content of:
#. <section><section><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: en/content/features/chat.xml:60
msgid "Controls whether or not agents should be able chat with each other."
msgstr "ChatEngine::ChatDirection::AgentToAgent"

#. type: Content of: <section><section><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: en/content/features/chat.xml:65
msgid ""
"ChatEngine::PermissionGroup::ChatReceivingAgents, "
"ChatEngine::PermissionGroup::ChatNotificationAgents, "
"ChatEngine::PermissionGroup::ChatStartingAgents"
msgstr "ChatEngine::PermissionGroup::ChatReceivingAgents, ChatEngine::PermissionGroup::ChatNotificationAgents, ChatEngine::PermissionGroup::ChatStartingAgents"

#. type: Content of:
#. <section><section><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: en/content/features/chat.xml:68
msgid ""
"Defines groups for the certain features. Receiving: Groups which can receive"
" and accept chat requests. Notification: Groups which can receive "
"notifications about new/pending chat requests. Starting: Groups which are "
"allowed to start new chats at all."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: en/content/features/chat.xml:73
msgid "ChatEngine::DefaultAgentName"
msgstr "ChatEngine::DefaultAgentName"

#. type: Content of:
#. <section><section><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: en/content/features/chat.xml:76
msgid ""
"A default name which should be displayed to customers and public users "
"instead of the real name of the chatting agents. If empty or disabled, the "
"real agent name will be shown."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: en/content/features/chat.xml:81
msgid "ChatEngine::DefaultAgentNameNumbers"
msgstr "ChatEngine::DefaultAgentNameNumbers"

#. type: Content of:
#. <section><section><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: en/content/features/chat.xml:84
msgid ""
"Controls whether or not numbers should be added to the agents default name "
"in case more than one agent is in a chat to allow customers/public users to "
"distinguish between the different agents (e.g. \"Support Agent 1\", "
"\"Support Agent 2\" etc.)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: en/content/features/chat.xml:89
msgid "ChatEngine::PublicInterface::AllowChatChannels"
msgstr "ChatEngine::PublicInterface::AllowChatChannels"

#. type: Content of:
#. <section><section><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: en/content/features/chat.xml:92
msgid ""
"Defines, if chat channel selection should be enabled for public users. If "
"set to \"no\", chats from public users will go to the default channel "
"automatically (ChatEngine::DefaultChatChannel)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: en/content/features/chat.xml:97
msgid "ChatEngine::PublicInterface::AvailabilityCheck"
msgstr "ChatEngine::PublicInterface::AvailabilityCheck"

#. type: Content of:
#. <section><section><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: en/content/features/chat.xml:100
msgid ""
"Defines, if chat channels should only be selectable in the public interface "
"if at least one agent with <link linkend=\"chat-permissions\">sufficient "
"permissions</link> is available in this channel."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: en/content/features/chat.xml:105
msgid "ChatEngine::CustomerInterface::AllowChatChannels"
msgstr "ChatEngine::CustomerInterface::AllowChatChannels"

#. type: Content of:
#. <section><section><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: en/content/features/chat.xml:108
msgid ""
"Defines, if chat channel selection should be enabled for customer users. If "
"set to \"no\", chats from customer users will go to the default channel "
"automatically (ChatEngine::DefaultChatChannel)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: en/content/features/chat.xml:113
msgid "ChatEngine::CustomerInterface::AvailabilityCheck"
msgstr "ChatEngine::CustomerInterface::AvailabilityCheck"

#. type: Content of:
#. <section><section><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: en/content/features/chat.xml:116
msgid ""
"Defines, if chat channels should only be selectable in the customer "
"interface if at least one agent with <link linkend=\"chat-"
"permissions\">sufficient permissions</link> is available in this channel."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: en/content/features/chat.xml:121
msgid "ChatEngine::CustomerThreshold"
msgstr "ChatEngine::CustomerThreshold"

#. type: Content of:
#. <section><section><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: en/content/features/chat.xml:124
msgid ""
"Amount of minutes which need to pass before a \"no agent is available\" "
"message is being displayed to the customer/public user who started the chat "
"request. The message can be configured using "
"ChatEngine::Texts::CustomerFrontend::NoAgentsAvailable::NewTicket or "
"ChatEngine::Texts::CustomerFrontend::NoAgentsAvailable::AddToExisiting "
"(customer interface) and "
"ChatEngine::Texts::PublicFrontend::NoAgentsAvailable (public interface)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: en/content/features/chat.xml:129
msgid "ChatEngine::AgentOnlineThreshold"
msgstr "ChatEngine::AgentOnlineThreshold"

#. type: Content of:
#. <section><section><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: en/content/features/chat.xml:132
msgid ""
"If an agent is not active in OTRS within this threshold, they will be "
"automatically set to \"unavailable for chat\" (see <link linkend=\"chat-"
"setup-availability\">\"Agents: Set up availability\"</link>)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: en/content/features/chat.xml:137
msgid "ChatEngine::DefaultChatChannel"
msgstr "ChatEngine::DefaultChatChannel"

#. type: Content of:
#. <section><section><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: en/content/features/chat.xml:140
msgid ""
"Name of the default chat channel. This channel must not be created manually "
"and can't be deleted. This channel is taken as target chat channel in case "
"chat channel selection is disabled for any interface."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: en/content/features/chat.xml:145
msgid "ChatEngine::ChatTTL"
msgstr "ChatEngine::ChatTTL"

#. type: Content of:
#. <section><section><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: en/content/features/chat.xml:148
msgid ""
"After how many hours a closed chat should be deleted from the database. "
"Closed chats can still be viewed and downloaded by customers. After a chat "
"has been deleted from the database, it will no longer be possible for "
"customers to view or download it."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: en/content/features/chat.xml:153
msgid "ChatEngine::ChatDecayTime"
msgstr "ChatEngine::ChatDecayTime"

#. type: Content of:
#. <section><section><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: en/content/features/chat.xml:156
msgid ""
"After how many days chats which are not closed should be deleted from the "
"database automatically in order to keep the database clean. Please note that"
" this setting can possibly delete chats which are still in use if they are "
"older than the configured amount of days."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: en/content/features/chat.xml:161
msgid "ChatEngine::ChatOrder"
msgstr "ChatEngine::ChatOrder"

#. type: Content of:
#. <section><section><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: en/content/features/chat.xml:164
msgid ""
"Defines, if new chats should be prepended or appended to the list of active "
"chats in the active chats widget in the chat manager."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><title>
#: en/content/features/chat.xml:172 en/content/features/video-calls.xml:46
msgid "Setup"
msgstr "Konfiguration"

#. type: Content of: <section><section><para>
#: en/content/features/chat.xml:174
msgid ""
"In order to be able to create your first chat, you need to setup certain "
"things in your OTRS instance."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><section><title>
#: en/content/features/chat.xml:177
msgid "Admin: Create chat channels and assign permissions"
msgstr "Admin: Erstellung von Chat-Kanälen und Zuweisen der Berechtigungen"

#. type: Content of: <section><section><section><para>
#: en/content/features/chat.xml:179
msgid ""
"In the admin area in OTRS, you'll find a new entry \"Chat Channel\" "
"(AdminChatChannel). Use this screen to add new channels. You'll need to "
"assign an existing agent group to each channel you'll create. You can use "
"the screens \"Agents &lt;-&gt; Groups\" or \"Agents &lt;-&gt; Roles\" to "
"assign permissions. There are new chat-specific permissions which are "
"described below."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><section><variablelist><title>
#: en/content/features/chat.xml:183
msgid "Available Chat Permissions"
msgstr "Verfügbare Chat-Berechtigungen"

#. type: Content of:
#. <section><section><section><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: en/content/features/chat.xml:185
msgid "CHAT_OBSERVER"
msgstr "CHAT_OBSERVER"

#. type: Content of:
#. <section><section><section><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: en/content/features/chat.xml:188
msgid ""
"Users with this permission type will only be able to observe chats in this "
"channel after they have been invited to them. They will not be able to "
"accept or observe chats in this channel on their own and if they are the "
"only agents currently available in this channel, customers/public users will"
" not be able to create a new chat in this channel. Observers can still "
"invite other agents to a chat they currently observe."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of:
#. <section><section><section><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: en/content/features/chat.xml:193
msgid "CHAT_PARTICIPANT"
msgstr "CHAT_PARTICIPANT"

#. type: Content of:
#. <section><section><section><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: en/content/features/chat.xml:196
msgid ""
"Users with this permission type will be able to take part in a chat, but "
"only after they get invited to it. After they're in a chat, they can change "
"the chat channel, discard the chat etc. They will not be able to accept a "
"customer/public user chat request on their own."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of:
#. <section><section><section><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: en/content/features/chat.xml:201
msgid "CHAT_OWNER"
msgstr "CHAT_OWNER"

#. type: Content of:
#. <section><section><section><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: en/content/features/chat.xml:204
msgid ""
"Users with this permission type will be able to accept chat customer/public "
"requests and do all kinds of observer and participant actions on a chat."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><section><note><para>
#: en/content/features/chat.xml:212
msgid ""
"To use the chat in general, agents still need to have at least ro "
"permissions to the groups set up in "
"ChatEngine::PermissionGroup::ChatReceivingAgents and "
"ChatEngine::PermissionGroup::ChatStartingAgents."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><section><title>
#: en/content/features/chat.xml:217
msgid "Agents: Select Active Chat Channels"
msgstr "Agenten: Auswahl der aktiven Chat-Kanäle"

#. type: Content of: <section><section><section><para><figure><title>
#: en/content/features/chat.xml:220
msgid "Setting up preferred chat channels"
msgstr "Auswahl der bevorzugten Chat-Kanäle"

#. type: Content of: <section><section><section><para><figure><screenshot>
#: en/content/features/chat.xml:222
msgid ""
"<graphic fileref=\"screenshots/chat/ChatAgentPrefChatChannels.png\" "
"scalefit=\"1\" width=\"100%\" contentdepth=\"100%\"></graphic>"
msgstr "<graphic fileref=\"screenshots/chat/ChatAgentPrefChatChannels.png\" scalefit=\"1\" width=\"100%\" contentdepth=\"100%\"></graphic>"

#. type: Content of: <section><section><section><para>
#: en/content/features/chat.xml:227
msgid ""
"As an agent, you'll need to select in which chat channels you want to be "
"available. Customers will only be able to create a new chat request on a "
"certain channel if at least one agent with owner permissions has selected "
"this channel in their preferences and is set as available for external chats"
" (see next section)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><section><title>
#: en/content/features/chat.xml:231
msgid "Agents: Set up Availability"
msgstr "Agenten: Einstellen der Verfügbarkeit"

#. type: Content of: <section><section><section><para><figure><title>
#: en/content/features/chat.xml:234
msgid "Setting up Chat Availability"
msgstr "Einstellen der Verfügbarkeit für Chatanfragen"

#. type: Content of: <section><section><section><para><figure><screenshot>
#: en/content/features/chat.xml:236
msgid ""
"<graphic fileref=\"screenshots/chat/ChatAgentToggleAvailability.png\" "
"scalefit=\"1\" width=\"100%\" contentdepth=\"100%\"></graphic>"
msgstr "<graphic fileref=\"screenshots/chat/ChatAgentToggleAvailability.png\" scalefit=\"1\" width=\"100%\" contentdepth=\"100%\"></graphic>"

#. type: Content of: <section><section><section><para>
#: en/content/features/chat.xml:241
msgid ""
"To be available for any chats, you'll need to use the chat toolbar switch. "
"It's a three-way switch with these states: unavailable for chats (empty "
"circle), available for internal (agent-to-agent) chats (empty circle with "
"tick sign), available for internal and external (customer-to-agent, public-"
"to-agent) chats (filled circle with tick sign). Just click the toggle in "
"order to change your availability."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><section><note><para>
#: en/content/features/chat.xml:245
msgid ""
"Your availability will be reset to \"internal chats only\" each time you log"
" in to OTRS again."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><title>
#: en/content/features/chat.xml:252
msgid "General Usage"
msgstr "Allgemeine Benutzung"

#. type: Content of: <section><section><section><title>
#: en/content/features/chat.xml:254
msgid "The Chat Manager"
msgstr "Die Chat-Verwaltung"

#. type: Content of: <section><section><section><para><figure><title>
#: en/content/features/chat.xml:257
msgid "The Chat Managing Screen"
msgstr "Die Chat-Verwaltungsübersicht"

#. type: Content of: <section><section><section><para><figure><screenshot>
#: en/content/features/chat.xml:259
msgid ""
"<graphic fileref=\"screenshots/chat/ChatManager.png\" scalefit=\"1\" "
"width=\"100%\" contentdepth=\"100%\"></graphic>"
msgstr "<graphic fileref=\"screenshots/chat/ChatManager.png\" scalefit=\"1\" width=\"100%\" contentdepth=\"100%\"></graphic>"

#. type: Content of: <section><section><section><para>
#: en/content/features/chat.xml:264
msgid ""
"The chat manager is the central point of the chat feature. As an agent, here"
" you can manage your chats and see and accept open requests. The chat "
"manager provides a list of chat requests from customers, public users and "
"other agents, as well as an overview over all active chats. Open the chat "
"manager by using \"Chat\" in the main navigation of OTRS."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><section><title>
#: en/content/features/chat.xml:269
msgid "Starting New Chats"
msgstr "Neue Chats beginnen"

#. type: Content of: <section><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/content/features/chat.xml:272
msgid "<emphasis>Agent to agent</emphasis>"
msgstr "<emphasis>Agent zu Agent</emphasis>"

#. type: Content of: <section><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/content/features/chat.xml:274
msgid ""
"To start a chat with another agent, you can use the user online widget from "
"the dashboard. Agents who are able to use the chat, will have a chat icon "
"next to their name which you can click on. Once clicked, a chat form will "
"open which you can use to enter your first chat message to this agent. After"
" the chat request has been sent to the other agent, you can watch the chat "
"in the chat manager."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/content/features/chat.xml:278
msgid "<emphasis>Agent to customer</emphasis>"
msgstr "<emphasis>Agent zu Kunde</emphasis>"

#. type: Content of: <section><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/content/features/chat.xml:280
msgid ""
"To start a chat with a customer, you can use the customer user widget from "
"the customer information center when viewing a certain customer. Online "
"customers will have a chat icon next to their name which you can click on. "
"Once clicked, a chat form will open which you can use to enter your first "
"chat message to this customer user. After the chat request has been sent to "
"the customer, you can watch the chat in the chat manager."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/content/features/chat.xml:283
msgid ""
"Another possibility is to create a chat from the ticket zoom. If the "
"customer user who is selected in this ticket is currently online, you'll be "
"able to use a chat icon next to their username in the customer information "
"box in right sidebar (see figure below)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of:
#. <section><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para><figure><title>
#: en/content/features/chat.xml:287
msgid "Starting an A2C chat from ticket zoom"
msgstr "Starten eines A2C Chat aus dem TicketZoom heraus"

#. type: Content of:
#. <section><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para><figure><screenshot>
#: en/content/features/chat.xml:289
msgid ""
"<graphic fileref=\"screenshots/chat/ChatTicketZoomStart.png\" scalefit=\"1\""
" width=\"100%\" contentdepth=\"100%\"></graphic>"
msgstr "<graphic fileref=\"screenshots/chat/ChatTicketZoomStart.png\" scalefit=\"1\" width=\"100%\" contentdepth=\"100%\"></graphic>"

#. type: Content of: <section><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/content/features/chat.xml:294
msgid ""
"Additionally, you will be able to start chat with customer users by clicking"
" on chat icons next to their name in the user online widget on the "
"dashboard."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of:
#. <section><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para><figure><title>
#: en/content/features/chat.xml:298
msgid "Starting an A2C chat from dashboard"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of:
#. <section><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para><figure><screenshot>
#: en/content/features/chat.xml:300
msgid ""
"<graphic fileref=\"screenshots/chat/ChatStartWidget.png\" scalefit=\"1\" "
"width=\"100%\" contentdepth=\"100%\"></graphic>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/content/features/chat.xml:306
msgid "<emphasis>Customer to agent</emphasis>"
msgstr "<emphasis>Kunde zu Agent</emphasis>"

#. type: Content of: <section><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/content/features/chat.xml:308
msgid ""
"Customers are not able to start a chat directly with a certain agent, but "
"only to create generic chat requests. To do this, customers can use the item"
" Chats → Create new chat from the customer interface main navigation."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of:
#. <section><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para><figure><title>
#: en/content/features/chat.xml:312
msgid "Starting a C2A chat"
msgstr "Starten eines C2A Chat"

#. type: Content of:
#. <section><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para><figure><screenshot>
#: en/content/features/chat.xml:314
msgid ""
"<graphic fileref=\"screenshots/chat/ChatCustomerNewRequest.png\" "
"scalefit=\"1\" width=\"100%\" contentdepth=\"100%\"></graphic>"
msgstr "<graphic fileref=\"screenshots/chat/ChatCustomerNewRequest.png\" scalefit=\"1\" width=\"100%\" contentdepth=\"100%\"></graphic>"

#. type: Content of: <section><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/content/features/chat.xml:320
msgid "<emphasis>Public to agent</emphasis>"
msgstr "<emphasis>Öffentlich zu Agent</emphasis>"

#. type: Content of: <section><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/content/features/chat.xml:322
msgid ""
"Users of the public interface are also not able to start a chat directly "
"with a certain agent, but only to create generic chat requests using the "
"public chat module (public.pl?Action=PublicChat). If you would like to "
"integrate the public chat module into your website, you can use the IsIframe"
" parameter. The OTRS header and footer will then be removed from the view "
"(public.pl?Action=PublicChat;IsIframe=1)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><section><title>
#: en/content/features/chat.xml:329
msgid "Handling Chat Requests"
msgstr "Umgang mit Chat-Anfragen"

#. type: Content of: <section><section><section><para>
#: en/content/features/chat.xml:331
msgid ""
"If there is a new chat request in one of the channels you (as an agent) have"
" permissions for, you'll receive a browser notification which allows you to "
"go directly to the chat manager. After you've opened the chat manager, you "
"can see a list of open requests of all types (see figure below)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><section><para><figure><title>
#: en/content/features/chat.xml:335
msgid "An Open Chat Request"
msgstr "Eine offene Chat-Anfrage"

#. type: Content of: <section><section><section><para><figure><screenshot>
#: en/content/features/chat.xml:337
msgid ""
"<graphic fileref=\"screenshots/chat/ChatNewRequest.png\" scalefit=\"1\" "
"width=\"100%\" contentdepth=\"100%\"></graphic>"
msgstr "<graphic fileref=\"screenshots/chat/ChatNewRequest.png\" scalefit=\"1\" width=\"100%\" contentdepth=\"100%\"></graphic>"

#. type: Content of: <section><section><section><para>
#: en/content/features/chat.xml:342
msgid ""
"Use the \"open chat\" button from the list to see the details of the "
"request. Clicking the button will open an overlay which provides several "
"actions on this request. Given that you've got sufficient permissions, you "
"can accept the request or change the channel for this request. Changing the "
"channel will follow the same rules as creating new request: you can only "
"move the request to a channel which has active agents in it."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><section><para>
#: en/content/features/chat.xml:345
msgid ""
"Changing the chat channel without accepting the request could be used to "
"dispatch chats to the right department for example."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><section><para><figure><title>
#: en/content/features/chat.xml:349
msgid "Open Chat Request Details"
msgstr "Details einer offenen Chat-Anfrage"

#. type: Content of: <section><section><section><para><figure><screenshot>
#: en/content/features/chat.xml:351
msgid ""
"<graphic fileref=\"screenshots/chat/ChatNewRequestDetail.png\" "
"scalefit=\"1\" width=\"100%\" contentdepth=\"100%\"></graphic>"
msgstr "<graphic fileref=\"screenshots/chat/ChatNewRequestDetail.png\" scalefit=\"1\" width=\"100%\" contentdepth=\"100%\"></graphic>"

#. type: Content of: <section><section><section><para>
#: en/content/features/chat.xml:356
msgid ""
"If you want to enter a chat, you can use the \"Accept\" button from the chat"
" detail overlay box. The chat will then be removed from the list of "
"requests, added to the list of your active chats and the customer/public "
"user will receive a message that you've entered the chat."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><section><title>
#: en/content/features/chat.xml:361
msgid "The Chat Widget"
msgstr "Das Chat-Widget"

#. type: Content of: <section><section><section><para><figure><title>
#: en/content/features/chat.xml:364 en/content/features/chat.xml:459
msgid "The chat widget"
msgstr "Das Chat-Widget"

#. type: Content of: <section><section><section><para><figure><screenshot>
#: en/content/features/chat.xml:366 en/content/features/chat.xml:461
msgid ""
"<graphic fileref=\"screenshots/chat/ChatWidget.png\" scalefit=\"1\" "
"width=\"100%\" contentdepth=\"100%\"></graphic>"
msgstr "<graphic fileref=\"screenshots/chat/ChatWidget.png\" scalefit=\"1\" width=\"100%\" contentdepth=\"100%\"></graphic>"

#. type: Content of: <section><section><section><para>
#: en/content/features/chat.xml:371
msgid ""
"The chat widget is the main component you'll use when chatting with other "
"people. It provides a history of all messages in the chat as well as list of"
" possible actions (depending on your permission level)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><section><para>
#: en/content/features/chat.xml:374
msgid ""
"To send messages, you can use the text field in the chat widget in your list"
" of active chats. Once you are done with typing your message, submit it by "
"either clicking the send icon next to the text field, or using tab and enter"
" (consecutively). When the message has been sent, the cursor will jump back "
"to the text field to allow for easily continuing to type."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><section><para>
#: en/content/features/chat.xml:377
msgid "Following you'll find a list of possible actions in the chat widget."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/content/features/chat.xml:381
msgid "<emphasis>Action: Monitor &amp; close</emphasis>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/content/features/chat.xml:383
msgid ""
"From the chat widget head top right hand side, you can close the chat by "
"clicking the \"x\" icon. Clicking the circle icon right next to the close "
"icon, allows you to set up a personal monitoring for this chat, which is "
"again a three-way switch (no monitoring = empty circle, only monitor "
"customer activity = empty circle with tick icon, monitor all actions = "
"filled circle with tick icon). When monitoring a chat, browser notifications"
" will show up each time there is a new action in this chat."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/content/features/chat.xml:386
msgid ""
"Also from the header, you can expand a toolbar of advanced chat actions for "
"this chat using the triangle icon. The toolbar also shows you the channel "
"this chat takes place in and which role you have in this chat (e.g. Owner)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of:
#. <section><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para><figure><title>
#: en/content/features/chat.xml:390
msgid "Monitor a chat"
msgstr "Einen Chat beobachten"

#. type: Content of:
#. <section><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para><figure><screenshot>
#: en/content/features/chat.xml:392
msgid ""
"<graphic fileref=\"screenshots/chat/ChatMonitorAndClose.png\" scalefit=\"1\""
" width=\"100%\" contentdepth=\"100%\"></graphic>"
msgstr "<graphic fileref=\"screenshots/chat/ChatMonitorAndClose.png\" scalefit=\"1\" width=\"100%\" contentdepth=\"100%\"></graphic>"

#. type: Content of:
#. <section><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para><figure><title>
#: en/content/features/chat.xml:398
msgid "Advanced chat actions"
msgstr "Weitere Chat-Aktionen"

#. type: Content of:
#. <section><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para><figure><screenshot>
#: en/content/features/chat.xml:400
msgid ""
"<graphic fileref=\"screenshots/chat/ChatAdvancedActions.png\" scalefit=\"1\""
" width=\"100%\" contentdepth=\"100%\"></graphic>"
msgstr "<graphic fileref=\"screenshots/chat/ChatAdvancedActions.png\" scalefit=\"1\" width=\"100%\" contentdepth=\"100%\"></graphic>"

#. type: Content of: <section><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/content/features/chat.xml:406
msgid "<emphasis>Action: Phone ticket</emphasis>"
msgstr "<emphasis>Aktion: Telefonticket</emphasis>"

#. type: Content of: <section><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/content/features/chat.xml:408
msgid ""
"Using the \"Phone ticket\" link from the advanced toolbar, allows you to "
"create a phone ticket to which the current chat will be appended to as an "
"article. After you've successfully created the ticket, the chat will get "
"closed automatically."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/content/features/chat.xml:412
msgid "<emphasis>Action: Append</emphasis>"
msgstr "<emphasis>Aktion: Hinzufügen</emphasis>"

#. type: Content of: <section><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/content/features/chat.xml:414
msgid ""
"Allows you to append this chat as an article to a selected ticket. After the"
" article has been created, the chat will get closed automatically."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/content/features/chat.xml:418
msgid "<emphasis>Action: Invite</emphasis>"
msgstr "<emphasis>Aktion: Einladen</emphasis>"

#. type: Content of: <section><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/content/features/chat.xml:420
msgid ""
"Allows you to invite another agent to this chat. You can select from a list "
"of available agents who you want to invite. Once you've invited the agent, a"
" new agent-to-agent chat request will be sent to this agent. After the "
"request has accepted, a new internal chat will be established between you "
"and the invited agent. In this internal chat, the invited agent has two more"
" actions available in the advanced actions toolbar: <link linkend=\"chat-"
"action-observer\">\"Observer\"</link> and <link linkend=\"chat-action-"
"participant\">\"Participant\"</link>."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/content/features/chat.xml:424
msgid "<emphasis>Action: Channel change</emphasis>"
msgstr "<emphasis>Aktion: Channel wechseln</emphasis>"

#. type: Content of: <section><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/content/features/chat.xml:426
msgid ""
"Using this link, you can change the channel for this chat. For the selection"
" of the target channel the same rules apply as for initially selecting a "
"chat channel."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/content/features/chat.xml:430
msgid "<emphasis>Action: Download</emphasis>"
msgstr "<emphasis>Aktion: Herunterladen</emphasis>"

#. type: Content of: <section><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/content/features/chat.xml:432
msgid "Lets you download the complete history of this chat as PDF."
msgstr "Lädt den kompletten Chatverlauf als PDF-Datei herunter"

#. type: Content of: <section><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/content/features/chat.xml:436
msgid "<emphasis>Action: New window</emphasis>"
msgstr "<emphasis>Aktion: Neues Fenster</emphasis>"

#. type: Content of: <section><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/content/features/chat.xml:438
msgid ""
"Opens this chat in a separate popup window. You can use this window in the "
"same way as the chat widget and both the widget and the popup can be used at"
" the same time."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/content/features/chat.xml:442
msgid "<emphasis>Action: Observer</emphasis>"
msgstr "<emphasis>Ation: Beobachten</emphasis>"

#. type: Content of: <section><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/content/features/chat.xml:444
msgid ""
"When you have been invited to a chat by another agent, you can decide if you"
" want to join the chat as observer or participant (depending on your "
"permission level). Once you click the action from your toolbar, a new chat "
"widget will be added to the list of your active chats which is the chat you "
"have been invited to. If you join the chat as observer, you will only be "
"able to read what others are contributing to the chat and you will be "
"invisible to customers or public users. Agents will still receive a message "
"that you joined the chat as observer. As an observer, you have the "
"possibility to become a participant anytime by using the advanced action "
"toolbar in your chat widget (depending on your permission level)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/content/features/chat.xml:448
msgid "<emphasis>Action: Participant</emphasis>"
msgstr "<emphasis>Aktion: Teilnehmer</emphasis>"

#. type: Content of: <section><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/content/features/chat.xml:450
msgid ""
"If you want to contribute something to the chat you have been invited to, "
"you can join it as a participant. Customers/public users and agents will "
"receive a message that you have entered the chat. As a participant, you can "
"become an observer anytime by using the advanced action toolbar in your chat"
" widget."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><section><title>
#: en/content/features/chat.xml:456
msgid "User availability"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><section><para>
